{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"all steps complete","closed_at":"2026-03-08T21:26:45Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"310e01c23c480b56fcc2f7ee520237d330a6ddc5376aa3633aecfa081cfcf21e","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:08:59Z","created_by":"Bernardo Kuri","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Refactor Village's ACP integration from daemon/HTTP model to stdio-first design.\n\n## Summary\nLocal ACP agents run as subprocesses communicating over stdio. Village should be directly spawnable by editors like Zed without daemon management.\n\n## Scope\n1. CLI Simplification - village acp runs stdio agent directly\n2. Permission Policies - auto + policy modes\n3. Model Selection - Map ACP modelId to Village LLM config\n4. Session Forking - Skip (keep NotImplementedError)\n5. Config Cleanup - Remove server_host/server_port\n6. Documentation - Update for stdio model\n\n## Out of Scope\n- HTTP transport (add when ACP spec supports remote)\n- Session forking\n- Interactive permission mode\n\n## Files\n- village/cli/acp.py\n- village/acp/agent.py\n- village/acp/bridge.py\n- village/acp/external_client.py\n- village/config.py\n- village/acp/permissions.py (new)\n- docs/ACP_*.md\n- tests/test_acp_*.py","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":660,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"bd-9fn","is_template":0,"issue_type":"epic","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"github@bkuri.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":1,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"ACP Refactor: Stdio-First Design","updated_at":"2026-03-08T21:26:45Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
